09:48.775 --> 09:50.775
Why are the police here?

09:50.777 --> 09:52.343
What's going on?

09:52.345 --> 09:55.046
Franco's giving us a statement.
He was just mugged.

09:55.048 --> 09:57.182
Gosh, if there was someone, anyone,

09:57.184 --> 09:59.017
who could help with a police sketch.

09:59.019 --> 10:00.985
Oh, here he is.

10:01.954 --> 10:03.788
Come on, y'all.
I already know who did it.

10:03.790 --> 10:05.290
It was Crackhead Kevin.

10:05.292 --> 10:06.925
Is that Crackhead Daryl's cousin?

10:06.927 --> 10:09.994
How many crackheads are in this family?

10:09.996 --> 10:11.729
There are six.

10:11.731 --> 10:13.998
We call 'em the Crackdashians.

10:16.202 --> 10:18.901
- We're still gonna need a description.
- Oh, come on!

10:18.926 --> 10:20.206
You're not gonna make him relive it.

10:20.231 --> 10:21.573
He's already been through enough.

10:21.575 --> 10:23.007
No, we're getting the money back.

10:23.009 --> 10:25.310
He was black, probably in his mid 30s.

10:25.312 --> 10:26.911
- Eye color? Hair color?
- Did he have

10:26.913 --> 10:29.981
any hobbies?
Soccer, fishing, gymnastics?

10:29.983 --> 10:32.650
Oh! Does he like bees?

10:32.652 --> 10:35.186
We'll call it in, but I got
to be honest with you guys,

10:35.188 --> 10:36.955
the odds of getting that money
back are pretty slim.

10:36.957 --> 10:39.858
Yeah, crackheads tend
to be impulse buyers.

10:39.860 --> 10:42.193
Of crack.

10:42.195 --> 10:44.496
No problem! It's only money!
R-Right? Right? Right?

10:44.498 --> 10:46.364
- Arthur, I'm gonna pay you back
- No.

10:46.366 --> 10:48.399
- every dime.
- No, don't be crazy.

10:48.401 --> 10:49.701
You haven't got that kind of money.

10:49.703 --> 10:51.874
No, but my Grandma CiCi
got me a savings bond

10:51.899 --> 10:53.843
